      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 38
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black. At its heart is the S54B32 high-revving straight-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. This example features the desirable Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory-spec limited-slip differential. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed: the double-VANOS system has been overhauled for precise cam timing, and the rear subframe mounting points have been reinforced to ensure structural integrity under lateral load. Suspension remains tight with refreshed rear trailing arm bushings (RTABs), maintaining the chassis's legendary communicative feedback. While displaying minor cosmetic patina consistent with a well-loved driver's car, the drivetrain and cooling system are in robust health. A visceral, analog performance machine optimized for the enthusiast who prioritizes mechanical excellence.",
      "price": 32500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 38
    },
    {
